<main class="about-content">

<h2>What this is</h2>
<p>
  The <em>Nanonets Landscape Monitor</em> is a curated, agent-generated
  intelligence dashboard tracking AI/ML developments relevant to the
  Nanonets document-AI stack. It is built by Claude Code agents running
  on a 6-hour cron — no human edits the output between builds.
</p>

<h2>How it's built</h2>
<p>
  Every six hours, a scheduled remote Claude Code agent runs a small
  Python pipeline in this repository. Ingestion fetches from arXiv,
  Hacker News, a curated list of RSS feeds, and GitHub trending. The
  agent then scores each item on four axes (Document AI, Competitive,
  Frontier, VLM research) using the editorial grounding in
  <code>data/nanonets_context.md</code>, writes "Implication for product
  / research / action" framings for the highest-ranked items, surfaces
  cross-item trend patterns, and emits questions for the Nanonets team
  in cases where the agent itself is uncertain. The agent commits the
  rendered HTML; GitHub Pages serves it.
</p>

<h2>What it covers — and what it doesn't</h2>
<p>
  <strong>Covered:</strong> arXiv (cs.CV / cs.CL / cs.LG / cs.AI),
  Hacker News (≥75 points + keyword filter), a curated RSS list
  (Anthropic, OpenAI, DeepMind, HuggingFace, Latent Space, Interconnects,
  AINews, Stratechery, Import AI, Mistral), and GitHub trending
  repositories.
</p>
<p>
  <strong>Not covered in v1:</strong> X / Twitter (no paid scraping
  path), Discord communities, private Slack workspaces, paywalled
  publications beyond their RSS-visible posts, and any source requiring
  authentication.
</p>

<h2>Attribution policy</h2>
<p>
  All items link directly to their source with <code>rel="nofollow noopener
  noreferrer"</code>. Summaries are limited to a single sentence each;
  no body excerpts beyond fair-use snippet length are reproduced. For
  paywalled sources (e.g., Stratechery, The Information), only the
  publicly-visible title and a generated summary are shown — body
  content is never re-hosted.
</p>

<h2>Not a Nanonets-corporate statement</h2>
<p>
  The editorial framing on this dashboard is generated by an autonomous
  AI agent. It does not represent positions of Nanonets, its leadership,
  or its DL team. Items are scored and described by the model's own
  reasoning; framing may be incorrect, biased, or out of date by the
  time you read it. Treat this as an analyst-grade newsfeed, not as
  Nanonets-corporate commentary.
</p>

<h2>Takedown / corrections</h2>
<p>
  If you'd like an item removed, a framing corrected, or feel your
  content is being misrepresented, please contact
  <a href="mailto:ali.shehral@gmail.com">ali.shehral@gmail.com</a>.
  Takedown requests are honored within 24 hours.
</p>

<h2>Status</h2>
<p>
  This dashboard is in active development. Indexing is currently
  disabled (<code>robots.txt: Disallow: /</code>) while the editorial
  format is reviewed by the Nanonets team. Public indexing will be
  enabled once the format is approved.
</p>

